      "author": "Jareika",
      "description": "New Features\r\n\r\n- **New Player Screen Controller window for all media**\r\n  - Every item you send to the Player Screen now opens its own tab in the controller, allowing you to switch between player‑screen content easily.\r\n  - Tabs can be closed individually. Clicking a closed tab again reopens it.\r\n  - Includes a dedicated button to close the Player Screen popout window.\r\n- **PDFs now use pdf.js in the Player Screen**\r\n  - PDFs sent to the Player Screen are rendered via pdf.js, enabling full PDF navigation from the controller.\r\n  - This feature was requested by users. Note that pdf.js increases the plugin size by a factor of ten and adds roughly 1.5 seconds to Obsidian’s startup time.\r\n    - For best performance, consider enabling it only during play sessions.\r\n- **Video control from the Player Screen Controller**\r\n  - Videos sent to the Player Screen can now be controlled directly from the controller (play, pause, seek, etc.).\r\n- **Send selected text to the Player Screen**\r\n  - Any highlighted text can now be sent directly to the player-facing display.\r\n- **New media search commands**\r\n  - Quickly search your vault for images, videos, or PDFs and send them to the Player Screen.",
      "downloadCount": 103,
      "draft": false,
